---
/**
 * lsm-compaction-deep-dive · Figure 3 — Level 2 "Size-tiered (STCS)": four small
 * same-size SSTables merge into one medium, four mediums into one large; the
 * SCORE box (write LOW, read MED–HI, space HIGH).
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/storage-engines/lsm-compaction-deep-dive.html
 * (figure + svg + figcaption). It lives as an .astro component, NOT inline in the
 * MDX, because MDX's JSX parser is unreliable with raw inline SVG that uses
 * kebab-case attributes (text-anchor, font-size, stroke-width, marker-end, …).
 *
 * The source page declared its arrowhead markers (#arw / #arwA / #arwG) ONCE in a
 * hidden top-of-body <svg defs>. Because each figure is now an isolated component,
 * the #arwA (fill #7a1f12) and #arw (fill #6b675f) markers this figure references
 * via marker-end="url(#…)" are inlined here in a local <defs> so it resolves
 * standalone (verbatim from the source defs).
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 560 200"
        role="img"
        aria-label="Size-tiered compaction: four small same-size SSTables merge into one medium, four mediums into one large, tiers grow geometrically"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arw"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#6b675f"></path></marker
            >
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
                ><path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path></marker
            >
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <text x="60" y="22" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f">small tier</text>
            <g fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ><rect x="20" y="32" width="34" height="20" rx="4"></rect><rect
                    x="60"
                    y="32"
                    width="34"
                    height="20"
                    rx="4"></rect><rect x="100" y="32" width="34" height="20" rx="4"></rect><rect
                    x="140"
                    y="32"
                    width="34"
                    height="20"
                    rx="4"></rect></g
            >
            <text x="97" y="46" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f">×4 same size</text
            >
            <line x1="97" y1="56" x2="97" y2="78" stroke="#7a1f12" marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
            <text x="160" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#7a1f12">merge</text>
            <text x="97" y="98" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#6b675f">medium tier</text
            >
            <g fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ><rect x="40" y="104" width="114" height="26" rx="4"></rect></g
            >
            <text x="97" y="121" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#1f3a5a">1 medium</text>
            <line
                x1="160"
                y1="117"
                x2="210"
                y2="117"
                stroke="#6b675f"
                stroke-dasharray="3 3"
                marker-end="url(#arw)"></line>
            <text x="186" y="110" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f">×4 → huge</text>
            <g fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a"
                ><rect x="218" y="100" width="150" height="34" rx="4"></rect></g
            >
            <text x="293" y="121" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >large tier</text
            >
            <!-- amp summary -->
            <rect
                x="392"
                y="28"
                width="158"
                height="142"
                rx="10"
                fill="#fbfaf2"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.4"></rect>
            <text
                x="471"
                y="48"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">SCORE</text
            >
            <text x="471" y="72" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#2f5d3a"
                >Write amp&#160;&#160;LOW</text
            >
            <text x="471" y="74" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                ><tspan x="471" dy="14">~log(N) rewrites</tspan></text
            >
            <text x="471" y="106" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >Read amp&#160;&#160;MED–HI</text
            >
            <text x="471" y="130" text-anchor="middle" font-size="11" fill="#9a2417"
                >Space amp&#160;&#160;HIGH</text
            >
            <text x="471" y="132" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8" fill="#6b675f"
                ><tspan x="471" dy="14">~2× during merge</tspan></text
            >
            <text x="200" y="166" text-anchor="middle" font-size="9" fill="#6b675f"
                >a key can sit in several un-merged tiers at once → duplicates linger</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        Tiers grow geometrically, so a key is rewritten only ~<code>log(N)</code> times — cheap writes.
        The bill is disk: a big merge briefly needs ~2× the dataset, and stale copies live across tiers.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
